-   The Three Main Categories of Fonts

Serif
    More professional and serious. Often used in books, newspapers, magazines...
"Georgia" and "Times New Roman" are one of the most popular Serif Fonts.

Sans-serif
    More playful and modern.
"Avenir", "Arial", "Futura", "Helvetica", "Roboto" are one of the most popular Sans-serif Fonts.

Monospace
    The fonts in this category have the same width for all their characters, ideal for displaying code.
"Consolas", "Courier", "Ubuntu" are one of the most popular Monospace Fonts.

-   System Font Stack
    These are the default fonts set depending on the current operating system, if you use them, your page's fonts will look different in every
operating system, but it'll provide a good user experience, because their browser won't have to download anything to display them.

font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;